    "name": math_eval,
    "arguments": {"expr": "100 * 3"},
    "result": 300.0
}
</tool_result>

To find the number of weeks, we divide the total pages by pages per week:<tool_call>
{
    "name": math_eval,
    "arguments": {"expr": "2100 / 300"}
}
</tool_call>
<tool_result>
{
    "name": math_eval,
    "arguments": {"expr": "2100 / 300"},
    "result": 7.0
}
</tool_result>

The opponent's calculation of 3 weeks is flawed because it incorrectly divides the total reading days by 7, treating every day as a reading day. This ignores Steve's actual schedule of reading only on Monday, Wednesday, and Friday.
